in South Dakota.

14:41.313 --> 14:44.283
{\an1}We talk a lot, but I haven't
seen him in a while.

14:44.350 --> 14:47.253
- He's the one that had that
article out a couple weeks ago.

14:47.319 --> 14:48.454
- Yeah, that would be him.

14:48.520 --> 14:50.956
This--that article
really bothered me

14:51.023 --> 14:53.292
because I talked to him
that day.

14:53.359 --> 14:56.528
- He was just bashing Matt
when they were--

14:56.595 --> 14:58.130
they've been talking
and [bleep],

14:58.197 --> 14:59.398
so it didn't make sense,

14:59.465 --> 15:01.500
and then we found out
that he was high.

15:01.567 --> 15:04.503
- Has he ever apologized
for that whole article?

15:04.570 --> 15:07.139
- Oh, yeah,
he apologized profusely,

15:07.206 --> 15:09.108
you know, and said,
"I was really high,"

15:09.174 --> 15:11.110
and, you know,
mentioned something about money,

15:11.176 --> 15:13.145
and apparently he did
not get paid,

15:13.212 --> 15:14.980
but I think he thought
he was going to.

15:15.047 --> 15:16.215
- When was the last time
you saw him?

15:16.282 --> 15:18.017
- Ten years.
- Ten years ago.

15:18.083 --> 15:19.451
- Yup. He got in some trouble,

15:19.518 --> 15:21.186
and he went to prison
for a little while,

15:21.253 --> 15:24.690
and it was tough
to keep in contact.

15:24.757 --> 15:26.158
I could have done a better job.

15:26.225 --> 15:30.162
I just selfishly didn't,
and I own that,

15:30.229 --> 15:33.198
but I'm not gonna
let that happen again

15:33.265 --> 15:35.134
now that we're--
now that we've reconnected.

15:35.200 --> 15:37.002
I can't let that happen again.

15:37.069 --> 15:44.176
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:49.114 --> 15:52.051
{\an8}<i>[upbeat music]</i>

15:52.117 --> 15:55.988
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:56.055 --> 15:58.057
{\an8}- [exclaiming]

15:58.123 --> 16:00.559
{\an8}- Okay, calm down.

16:00.626 --> 16:04.463
{\an8}<i>- ♪ I took my sorrow</i>
<i>to a foreign field ♪</i>

16:04.530 --> 16:08.467
<i>♪ Hoping I could find myself ♪</i>

16:08.534 --> 16:13.072
<i>♪ Oh, and if I ever find</i>
<i>my way home ♪</i>

16:13.138 --> 16:17.109
<i>♪ Will you tell me</i>
<i>it was all a dream? ♪</i>

16:17.176 --> 16:21.613
<i>♪ Oh, oh-oh-oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

16:21.680 --> 16:25.351
<i>♪ Oh, oh-oh-oh,</i>
<i>oh-oh-oh, oh ♪</i>

16:26.752 --> 16:29.655
{\an1}- How's the planning for
Butch's surprise party going?

16:29.722 --> 16:31.457
- It's going good.

16:31.523 --> 16:34.360
{\an8}- I just wanted to check in
and see how you were doing.

16:34.426 --> 16:37.262
{\an8}- How I'm doing?

16:37.329 --> 16:39.698
It's not about me.

16:39.765 --> 16:42.568
- Has she been sleeping a lot?
- No, except yesterday.

16:42.634 --> 16:44.503
{\an3}She took a nap
on the couch yesterday.

16:44.570 --> 16:46.605
And now she's laying there
doing whatever she's doing.

16:46.672 --> 16:49.241
{\an1}- Because of how bad it got last
time, like, does it scare you

16:49.308 --> 16:51.643
{\an1}that she's starting
to feel this way again?

16:51.710 --> 16:53.379
- No, 'cause I think

16:53.445 --> 16:57.683
{\an3}she's got the right tools
to figure it out this time.

16:57.750 --> 16:59.518
- That's good.

16:59.585 --> 17:01.387
- I stay out of it.

17:01.453 --> 17:03.155
- It's got to be hard for you.

17:03.222 --> 17:05.656
- No, it's not hard for me.
- To stay out of it?

17:05.723 --> 17:06.724
- Yeah.
- Really?

17:06.791 --> 17:08.460
{\an3}- Yeah.

17:08.527 --> 17:12.097
{\an3}It'd be different if what
I said helps, but it doesn't.

17:12.164 --> 17:14.098
It makes things worse,

17:14.165 --> 17:15.733
so I'm just not nice enough.

17:15.800 --> 17:17.636
I can't say it nice enough.

17:17.703 --> 17:20.372
It's just annoying.
Like, dude, come on.

17:22.241 --> 17:24.443
I don't understand.

17:24.510 --> 17:26.444
{\an1}- But you're working on that
with Kathleen, right?

17:26.512 --> 17:29.481
{\an3}- Yeah, I mean, we're trying,
but it's just like...

17:29.548 --> 17:31.116
{\an3}I'm kind of--that's
one thing that I'm learning,

17:31.183 --> 17:32.584
{\an3}I guess, is learning
when it's, like,

17:32.651 --> 17:34.787
{\an3}"Nope, Tyler, you're not gonna
say it the right way,

17:34.853 --> 17:36.488
so don't say nothing at all."

17:36.555 --> 17:43.495
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:45.631 --> 17:47.199
{\an8}<i>[line trilling]</i>

17:47.266 --> 17:49.601
{\an8}- Hi, Kiana.
<i>- [speaking indistinctly]</i>

17:49.668 --> 17:50.836
{\an8}- Yeah, I certainly can.

17:50.903 --> 17:52.571
{\an8}Didn't know you were there.
Buh-bye.

17:52.638 --> 17:53.372
{\an8}<i>- Okay, bye.</i>

17:53.439 --> 17:56.175
{\an8}- Someone showed up early
to work.

17:56.241 --> 17:58.544
{\an8}- Who is that?
Kiana?

17:58.610 --> 18:01.513
{\an9}- "Can I disarm the alarm
with an attitude?"

18:01.580 --> 18:03.582
- Can you see her on camera?
- Yeah.

18:03.649 --> 18:05.217
{\an3}Doesn't look like
a happy employee, though.

18:05.284 --> 18:06.685
- Nuh-uh.
- So anyways, Soph,

18:06.752 --> 18:08.420
I got to drop you off,
'cause the guy's gonna

18:08.487 --> 18:09.655
deliver the inventory.

18:09.721 --> 18:12.591
- [playing organ notes
on keyboard]

18:12.658 --> 18:14.793
[door closes]
- All right, let's go.

18:14.860 --> 18:17.796
- [holding one note on keyboard]

18:17.863 --> 18:20.866
{\an8}<i>[upbeat music]</i>

18:20.933 --> 18:24.703
{\an8}<i>- ♪ I see you ♪</i>

18:24.770 --> 18:26.872
{\an8}<i>♪ I see you ♪</i>

18:26.939 --> 18:28.774
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:28.841 --> 18:30.275
{\an3}- Here.

18:30.342 --> 18:32.878
{\an3}Kiana, why didn't you open
up the door

18:32.945 --> 18:35.514
for the inventory guy?

18:35.581 --> 18:37.549
Here let me--
you with this.

18:39.852 --> 18:41.653
{\an8}- Thank you so much.

18:45.557 --> 18:47.626
{\an3}Okay, so we got to hurry up,
get this open,

18:47.693 --> 18:50.362
and then we're gonna have
a talk outside

18:50.429 --> 18:52.431
because I can't, like, talk

18:52.498 --> 18:53.899
{\an1}with all this distraction
going on,

18:53.966 --> 18:55.501
